# Editor State (Zustand)

Single store: `useEditorStore` in `src/stores/editor-store.ts`. Holds `meta` (map metadata), `buildings`, `drawing`, `view`, `history`, `isSaving`, `isDirty`.

## Building shape

A `Building` (`src/types/index.ts`) has: `id`, `mapId`, `name`, `abbreviation`, `category`, `polygonPoints`, `centerX/Y`, optional `description`, `floors`, `departments`, `color`, `imageUrl`, plus required `sortOrder` and `locked`. When you add a field, update the type, all defaults in the store, the BuildingForm UI, and the save payload in `MapEditor.handleSave`.

## History rules

- Mutations that produce a single discrete change push history via `pushHistory(history, currentBuildings)` **before** updating buildings.
- For continuous interactions (dragging a polygon body or vertex), the caller takes a snapshot once at the start via `pushHistorySnapshot(currentBuildings)` and then calls `moveBuilding`/`updateBuilding` repeatedly without further snapshots until the gesture ends. See `EditorCanvas.tsx`'s `onMoveStart` / `onMove` props.

## Save payload

`MapEditor.handleSave` builds the buildings payload manually. Every persisted field must be listed there - missing a field silently strips it on save. See the `database.mdc` rule.

## Import / export

`importBuildings(items, mode)` in the store generates fresh IDs, rebinds `mapId` to the current map (or `"new"`), recomputes centroids when missing, defaults colors per category, and resets `sortOrder` by array index. The exported JSON file must therefore be portable - never include `id` or `mapId` in exports.
